snippet.textDisplay:
Worlds cheapest carbon fiber rods, https://photos.app.goo.gl/vyNCmkWJGR1F4bFAA
What you could do is put paper in checker board on a table.  Put some styrofoam with bricks to hold them down to dry, and overlap 50%.  Repeat ten times with glue, or even water, but definitely finish with sealer.  Its not impossibly strong, but around 20ft pounds dry without glue.

I'm making some 48in 3/16 dowels with 30in postal wrap.  Its way more difficult, its about 100 times harder, you have to pre-roll the dowels because the paper won't roll by itself.  So I got them down to inch, let them sit for a week, then try a quarter inch, lol!
